Glencore, Spain’s Cepsa in Talks Over Oil Accord, Expansion Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-12-01T08:06:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/glencore-spain-s-cepsa-in-talks-over-oil-accord-expansion-says.html
Cepsa, a Spanish  oil company , and
Switzerland-based  Glencore International Plc  are in talks to
collaborate in the oil industry,  Expansion  reported, citing
unidentified people in the industry.  The potential alliance, which has been promoted by Cepsa’s
and Glencore’s common shareholder, International Petroleum
Investment Co. of  Abu Dhabi , may be focused on commercial and
logistics agreements, without ruling out selling and buying
asset stakes or joint investments, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
